<p>The <code>like</code> function performs SQL LIKE pattern matching (% = any chars, _ = single char).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'test.txt' | like('%.txt'){close}</pre>
<p>Matches *.txt: <b>{'test.txt' | like('%.txt')}</b> (1 = true)</p>

<pre>{open}'test.pdf' | like('%.txt'){close}</pre>
<p>Matches *.txt: <b>{'test.pdf' | like('%.txt')}</b> (empty = false)</p>

<h2>Pattern Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}'hello' | like('h%'){close}</pre>
<p>Starts with h: <b>{'hello' | like('h%')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'hello' | like('%lo'){close}</pre>
<p>Ends with lo: <b>{'hello' | like('%lo')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'hello' | like('%ell%'){close}</pre>
<p>Contains ell: <b>{'hello' | like('%ell%')}</b></p>

<h2>Single Character Wildcard</h2>
<pre>{open}'test1' | like('test_'){close}</pre>
<p>test + 1 char: <b>{'test1' | like('test_')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'test12' | like('test_'){close}</pre>
<p>test + 1 char: <b>{'test12' | like('test_')}</b> (no match - 2 chars)</p>

<h2>File Filtering</h2>
<pre>{open}$samplePath | like('%.txt'){close}</pre>
<p>Is .txt file: <b>{$samplePath | like('%.txt')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}$samplePath | afterLast('/') | like('file%'){close}</pre>
<p>Filename starts with 'file': <b>{$samplePath | afterLast('/') | like('file%')}</b></p>
